cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about designing a light-weight network for video attention prediction, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a knowledge distillation strategy to train the network effectively, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves processing and analyzing multimedia data, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which is related to neural networks, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
